Renaissance Technologies LLC Sells 2,187,500 Shares of Avon Products, Inc. (AVP)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 

Renaissance Technologies LLC decreased its position in Avon Products, Inc. (NYSE:AVP) by 27.6% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The fund owned 5,732,800 shares of the company’s stock after selling 2,187,500 shares during the period. Renaissance Technologies LLC’s holdings in Avon Products were worth $25,224,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also bought and sold shares of the company. Credit Agricole S A purchased a new position in shares of Avon Products during the fourth quarter worth approximately $104,000. Acrospire Investment Management LLC raised its position in shares of Avon Products by 33.7% in the first quarter. Acrospire Investment Management LLC now owns 24,036 shares of the company’s stock worth $106,000 after buying an additional 6,058 shares in the last quarter. A.R.T. Advisors LLC purchased a new position in shares of Avon Products during the fourth quarter worth approximately $111,000. Point View Wealth Management Inc. raised its position in shares of Avon Products by 4.0% in the first quarter. Point View Wealth Management Inc. now owns 25,485 shares of the company’s stock worth $112,000 after buying an additional 981 shares in the last quarter. Finally, Parametrica Management Ltd raised its position in shares of Avon Products by 119.7% in the first quarter. Parametrica Management Ltd now owns 29,338 shares of the company’s stock worth $129,000 after buying an additional 15,985 shares in the last quarter. 86.90% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 




Avon Products, Inc. (AVP) traded up 0.27% during trading on Thursday, reaching $3.65. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 4,709,988 shares. The stock has a 50-day moving average price of $3.62 and a 200 day moving average price of $4.37. Avon Products, Inc. has a 52-week low of $3.24 and a 52-week high of $6.96. The company’s market cap is $1.61 billion. 


 Get Avon Products Inc. alerts:



Avon Products (NYSE:AVP) last released its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, May 4th. The company reported ($0.07) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.01 by $0.08. Avon Products had a negative return on equity of 3.68% and a net margin of 0.26%. The firm had revenue of $1.33 billion during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $1.33 billion. During the same period in the prior year, the firm posted ($0.07) earnings per share. Avon Products’s revenue for the quarter was up 2.0% compared to the same quarter last year. On average, analysts expect that Avon Products, Inc. will post $0.22 EPS for the current year. 
