ve on shares of ABB and gave the company a "sell" rating in a report on Monday, July 3rd. The company had revenue of $8.45 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $8.55 billion. The average 1-year price target among analysts that have covered the stock in the last year is $23.00. ABB had a return on equity of 18.62% and a net margin of 6.87%. If you are reading this piece on another domain, it was copied illegally and republished in violation of USA and worldwide trademark and copyright legislation. During the same quarter in the previous year, the firm posted $0.35 earnings per share.TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: "ABB Ltd (ABB) Shares Bought by Fisher Asset Management LLC" was originally posted by Chaffey Breeze and is owned by of Chaffey Breeze. Pennsylvania Trust Co purchased a new position in shares of ABB during the second quarter worth approximately $222,000. The correct version of this article can be read at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/23/abb-ltd-abb-shares-bought-by-fisher-asset-management-llc-updated.html. The Company's segments include Electrification Products, Robotics and Motion, Industrial Automation, Power Grids, and Corporate and Other.


